Variables:

variableName=value

Variables are accessed using $
example: echo $variableName

---

Local variables:

functionName() {
        local greeting="Hello World!"
}


- Variables defined inside functions and can only be used in that functon.

---

Arrays:

arrayName=("value1" "value2" "value3") || Creates an array with three values

${arrayName[n]} || Access value n in array.

arrayName[n]="newValue" || Modifies array element n with new value.

---

Parameters:

$# : The number of arguments passed.
$0 : The name of the script.
$n : n is position of the arguments when executing the script/function.
$@ : All parameters.
